Choose relevant visuals that effectively convey the information and support your main message. Pay attention to color schemes, fonts, and overall design aesthetics to create a cohesive and visually pleasing look.

Evaluate the visual elements to ensure they effectively convey the information and maintain visual appeal. Seek feedback from others to gain different perspectives and identify areas for improvement. Make necessary revisions and refinements based on the feedback received.


7. Export and publish: Export your completed infographic in a suitable file format, ensuring compatibility with different platforms and devices. Choose appropriate platforms to publish and share your infographic, considering the preferences and habits of your target audience. Provide an accompanying description or caption that provides context and encourages engagement.

uiyK0hoOaMBcJ0WwqEQK.prompts:
Enhance the offer using the Scarcity, Urgency, Bonuses and Guarantees outlined below for PRODUCT, MARKET and AUDIENCE.

Fill the following template:

-- Scarcity --
There are 3 types of scarcity:
- Limited Supply of Seats/Slots: in general or over X period of time.
- Limited Supply of Bonuses
- Never available again.

{{Generate 10 ideas on how to increase scarcity. Be creative, unique and tap into unique emotions.}}

{{Generate 5 more ideas on how to increase scarcity by mixing 2 or 3 of the types of scarcity above.}}

-- Urgency --
There are 3 types of urgency:
- Rolling Cohorts: when you start clients on a rolling basis such as weekly, monthly, quarterly, etc.
- Rolling Seasonal Urgency: use an actual signup date with a deadline and different promotion based on the season.
- Promotional or Pricing Urgency: increasing the price with a deadline or making bonuses available only until a specific deadline.

{{Generate 10 ideas on how to increase urgency. Be creative, unique and tap into unique emotions.}}

{{Generate 5 more ideas on how to increase urgency by mixing 2 or 3 of the types of urgency above.}}

-- Bonuses --
The main point to take away from this is that a single offer is less valuable than the same offer broken into its component parts and stacked as bonuses. This section is about how to present the pieces of what you offer in a good order. These bonuses can be checklists, tools, swipe files, scripts, templates, etc.

{{Create a list of 15 jaw-dropping, unique, highly valuable bonuses that would help overcome potential objections, solve their problems and significantly increase the perceived value of the product.}}

{{Create a list of 10 partnership bonuses. These bonuses are meant to be complementary to your product. You can get other businesses to give you their services and products as a part of your bonuses in exchange for exposure to your clients for free. This is free marketing for them, and high value products for you at no cost. Businesses will do this because you are going to give their business exposure for free to the highest quality prospects, your customers.}}

-- Guarantee --

There are 4 types of guarantees:
- Unconditional Guarantees
- Conditional Guarantees: Conditional guarantees include “terms and conditions” to the guarantee. These are the ones you can get VERY creative on. In general, you want these to be “better than money back” guarantees. Because if they are going to make an investment, you want to match their investment psychologically with an equal or higher perceived commitment.
- Anti-Guarantees: when you explicitly state “all sales are final.” You will want to own this position. You must come up with a creative “reason why” the sales are final. 
- Implied Guarantees: An offer that is a performance-based offer. This comes in many different forms. Revenue share, profit share, triggers, ratchets, monetary bonuses, etc are all examples.

{{Create a list of 10 jaw-dropping, unique, highly valuable guarantees that would help convert more customers that are on the fence.}}

Additional tips - 
Ultimately, you will use these 5 amplifiers this way:
- Use scarcity to decrease supply to raise prices (and indirectly increase demand through perceived exclusiveness)
- Use urgency to increase demand by decreasing the action threshold of a prospect.
- Use bonuses to increase demand (and increase perceived exclusivity).
- Use guarantees to increase demand by reversing risk.
- Use names to re-stimulate demand and expand awareness of my offer to my target audience.
